The article discusses the author's experience attending a ceremony at the White House to honor the officers and first responders involved in the shooting in Alexandria, Virginia, on June 14, 2017. President Donald J. Trump awarded Medals of Valor to two Capitol Police officers and three Alexandria Police Officers for their heroic actions in saving lives during the incident. The author, who is a participant in the Summer 2017 White House Internship Program, describes the event as a touching and memorable experience, as they had the opportunity to meet and thank the officers and their families. The author also reflects on their time as a White House intern, expressing gratitude for the privilege of serving the American people and witnessing important events.